China's endangered panda expands habitatATTENTION - ADDS information on sub-species of giant panda ///
Hunger-threatened giant pandas in China to be moved to new food source
China applies to United Nations for protection of panda's natural habitat
About 100 giant pandas in northwest China's Gansu Province are suffering from hunger becauselarge tracts of arrow bamboo have bloomed and died.
The discovery of panda traces in Fengxian County, northwest China's Shaanxi Province, demonstrates that the habitat of the rare creatures is expanding in this inlandprovince, an official with the Shaanxi Provincial Forestry Bureau said.
